      "rationale": "NIH and derived RH index are the regulatory-accepted hemolysis metrics for CPB devices per FDA guidance. RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly maps to COU decision. Shear stress history integrated via power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen–Wurzinger). Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the device geometry, operating range, and fluid conditions representative of CPB COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at CPB-relevant flow rates (4–7 L/min) and rotational speeds (2500–4500 RPM). Blood analogue and porcine blood used. Geometry fidelity confirmed by CT scan comparison. Validation scope judged adequate for MRL 2. Note: validation test matrix does not include operating points dominated by low-shear recirculation, where the omitted non-Newtonian rheology would be most influential; this gap was noted informally but not formally characterised."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence monitored; residuals and QoI monitors confirm solution convergence.",
      "rationale": "Scaled residuals < 1e-5 for all equations; NIH monitor flat over final 500 iterations. Steady-state MRF approach used for impeller rotation. Convergence confirmed for all 5 operating points. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition inputs verified against test data.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of CFD setup completed by second analyst. Boundary conditions cross-checked against experimental records. No errors identified. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis model selection justified with reference to literature and validation evidence.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published rotating machinery validation studies. Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model adopted per FDA guidance. Blood modelled as single-phase incompressible Newtonian fluid (constant viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s). Non-Newtonian shear-thinning behaviour (Carreau–Yasuda) is present in real blood at low shear rates but is excluded from the model on the basis that high-shear regions dominate hemolysis contribution; this exclusion was reviewed informally during team discussion and judged acceptable, though no formal fidelity trade study or documented sensitivity analysis quantifying the impact of this abstraction is included in the evidence package. Model form assessment judged adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) traceable to measurement data or literature with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry from manufacturer CAD with dimensional inspection report. Fluid density 1050 kg/m³ and Newtonian viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s from literature (Merrill 1969). Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream piping geometry. All inputs documented in simulation data package. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
