  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scope. Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hydraulic performance within 3.2% MAE and hemolysis index within 8.7% NRMSE against experimental benchmarks. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all validation operating points. The team concluded the evidence package provides sufficient credibility for the COU decision to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. The model's use of Newtonian blood rheology, excluding non-Newtonian shear-thinning effects present in the physical system, was considered during deliberation; the team noted informally that sensitivity to this choice was studied informally and deemed low given high-shear dominance of hemolysis, but acknowledged no formal sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study is documented. The overall evidence package is judged adequate at Medium assurance level for a Class II device at MRL 2.",
